    "body": "We have an [IncreasingPriceCrowdsale](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blob/v1.9.0/contracts/crowdsale/price/IncreasingPriceCrowdsale.sol) that grows linearly, but shows how `getCurrentRate` can be used for more interesting functions. @misteraverin are you still interesting in contributing here? If so, let us know how we can help you.\r\n\r\nFTR, there's also some experimentation with [BondingCurves](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/issues/819), which adjust the rate of the token and can be used to incentivize or disincentivize different things. This could be more interesting than a hard-coded stepped rate.",
